<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.scottjoplin.org" class="external text" title="http://www.scottjoplin.org" rel="nofollow">The Scott Joplin International Ragtime Foundation</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.stlouiswalkoffame.org/inductees/scott-joplin.html" class="external text" title="http://www.stlouiswalkoffame.org/inductees/scott-joplin.html" rel="nofollow">Joplin at St. Louis Walk of Fame</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.perfessorbill.com/pbmidi15.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.perfessorbill.com/pbmidi15.shtml" rel="nofollow">"Perfessor" Bill Edwards plays Joplin</a>, with anecdotes and research.</li>
<li><a href="http://music.minnesota.publicradio.org/features/9905_ragtime/index.shtml#timeline" class="external text" title="http://music.minnesota.publicradio.org/features/9905_ragtime/index.shtml#timeline" rel="nofollow">Maple Leaf Rag</a> A site dedicated to 100 years of the Maple Leaf Rag.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mostateparks.com/scottjoplin.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.mostateparks.com/scottjoplin.htm" rel="nofollow">The Scott Joplin House - St. Louis, Missouri</a></li>
</ul>
<p><a name="Recordings_and_sheet_music" id="Recordings_and_sheet_music"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Scott_Joplin&amp;action=edit&amp;section=34" title="Edit section: Recordings and sheet music">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Recordings and sheet music</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://kreusch-sheet-music.net/eng/?page=show&amp;query=Scott%20Joplin&amp;order=op" class="external text" title="http://kreusch-sheet-music.net/eng/?page=show&amp;query=Scott%20Joplin&amp;order=op" rel="nofollow">www.kreusch-sheet-music.net</a> - Free Scores by Joplin</li>
<li><a href="http://www.MutopiaProject.org/cgibin/make-table.cgi?searchingfor=Joplin" class="external text" title="http://www.MutopiaProject.org/cgibin/make-table.cgi?searchingfor=Joplin" rel="nofollow">The Mutopia project</a> has freely downloadable piano scores of several of Joplin's works</li>
<li><a href="http://www.ragtimepiano.ca/rags/joplin.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ragtimepiano.ca/rags/joplin.htm" rel="nofollow">Sheet Music and Covers</a> (includes cover art, comprehensive sheet music selection, and biography)</li>
<li><a href="http://icking-music-archive.org/ByComposer/Joplin.php" class="external text" title="http://icking-music-archive.org/ByComposer/Joplin.php" rel="nofollow">Free scores</a> by Scott Joplin in the <a href="/wiki/Werner_Icking_Music_Archive" title="Werner Icking Music Archive">Werner Icking Music Archive (WIMA)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.imslp.org/wiki/Category:Joplin,_Scott" class="extiw" title="scores:Category:Joplin, Scott">Free scores by Scott Joplin</a> in the <a href="/wiki/International_Music_Score_Library_Project" title="International Music Score Library Project">International Music Score Library Project</a></li>
<li>Kunst der Fuge: <a href="http://www.kunstderfuge.com/ragtime.htm#Joplin" class="external text" title="http://www.kunstderfuge.com/ragtime.htm#Joplin" rel="nofollow">Scott Joplin - MIDI files</a> (live and piano-rolls recordings)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.free-sheet-music.de/joplin" class="external text" title="http://www.free-sheet-music.de/joplin" rel="nofollow">Scott Joplin</a> - German site with free sheet music and MIDI files</li>
<li><a href="http://www.johnroachemusic.com/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.johnroachemusic.com/index.html" rel="nofollow">John Roache's site</a> has excellent MIDI performances of ragtime music by Joplin and others</li>
<li>Scott Joplin, Complete Piano Rags, David A Jasen, 1988, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0486258076" class="internal">ISBN 0-486-25807-6</a></li>
<li><a href="http://sheetmusicswap.com/music.php?composer=1" class="external text" title="http://sheetmusicswap.com/music.php?composer=1" rel="nofollow">Scott Joplin Sheet Music</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.pianola.co.nz/sounds/Pleasant_Moments_Piano_Roll.mp3" class="external text" title="http://www.pianola.co.nz/sounds/Pleasant_Moments_Piano_Roll.mp3" rel="nofollow">Pleasant Moments, 2.1MB</a>. This is a recording of the Connorized piano roll made by Joplin in April 1916, and thought lost until mid-2006.</li>
</ul>


